title: General Ledger, 1882-1885
note_with_search_term: This ledger includes cash and commission accounts as well as special accounts, including holdings of bonds. Note the lettering in the headings. Identified as National Bank of Washington on basis of cover and existence of general ledger for Riggs & Co. for this year.

title: Trust, 1892-1952
note_with_search_term: Consists of Washington Loan and Trust trust department account ledgers and paper files, estate files, a trust department real estate holdings ledger, and trust department and committee minutes.

title: Financial records, 1982-1990
note_with_search_term:
This series contains records related to the Burns Clinic expansion, Square 250 leases/construction, 1925 F Street, 2000 Penn. Avenue taxes, and other real estate holdings. These records cover the dates 1982-90.

Formerly ACC#566.

title: Television News Study Center and projects, 1975 ca.-1987
note_with_search_term: This series contains guides, memorandums, news articles, news releases, an invitation, correspondence, and brochures. The materials range in date from approximately 1975 to 1987. They cover the holdings of the Media Resources Department, transcription projects, and the Television News Study Center. Formerly vertical files

title: Larry King show, 1970-ca. 1990
note_with_search_term: 10 unprocessed boxes were moved from the Larry King series to the Jim Bohanan series.
